  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empower Sri Lankan Youth at Vocational Fish Farm</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Kalapuwa Sri Sustainable Fish Farm Project provides critical vocational training opportunities to the 195 orphaned children, some traumatized by the civil war or tsunami, that are cared for at the Kalapuwa &amp; Samudra Sri Leadership Academies. The region surrounding Kalapuwa Sri derives its income primarily from a fishing industry and this project will build a new fish processing facility that will add greatly to the scope of the existing vocational training program that empowers our students.</narrative>
  </description>
